tly one output file at `output_path`\n    37 - no reads from other experiment result files\n    38 \n    39 ## 0.0 Agent Execution Contract\n    40 \n    41 This section is for the receiving agent.\n    42 \n    43 If a user tells you to use this file to run one experiment cell, do not ask them to restate the whole methodology if the minimum metadata is already present.\n    44 \n    45 When invoked with:\n    46 - `run_profile_id`\n    47 - `prompt_id`\n    48 - `condition` if explicitly specified\n    49 \n    50 you must:\n    51 1. resolve model metadata from `## 0.5 Default Run Profile Catalog`\n    52 2. resolve prompt text and designated tools from `## 0.6 Canonical Prompt Catalog`\n    53 3. if `condition` is omitted, infer the next missing condition in this order:\n    54    `baseline` -> `prompted` -> `critique_initial` -> `tool_review` -> `critique_revised`\n    55 4. if `date` is omitted, use the local current date\n    56 5. if `output_path` is omitted, derive it from `## 5. Recommended Output Path Pattern`\n    57 6. if `condition = tool_review` and `critique_initial_path` is omitted, derive the canonical same-cell path\n    58 7. if `condition = critique_revised` and upstream paths are omitted, derive the canonical same-cell paths\n    59 8. choose the correct wrapper from `## 1` or `## 2`\n    60 9. execute exactly one cell\n    61 10. write only the final artifact to `output_path`\n    62 \n    63 Do not ask the user for:\n    64 - `date` if it was omitted\n    65 - `output_path` if it was omitted\n    66 - `condition` if the next missing condition can be inferred safely\n    67 \n    68 Ask only if one of these is truly missing or ambiguous:\n    69 - `run_profile_id`\n    70 - `prompt_id`\n    71 - a required upstream artifact for the inferred cell\n    72 \n    73 If `condition = tool_review`, you also need either:\n    74 - `critique_initial_answer`, or\n    75 - `critique_initial_path`\n    76 \n    77 If `condition = critique_revised`, you also need either:\n    78 - `critique_initial_answer` and `critique_packet`, or\n    79 - `critique_initial_path` and `tool_review_path`\n    80 \n    81 Permitted file reads:\n    82 - you may read this file\n    83 - you may read the specific upstream artifact files explicitly named in the handoff for the same cell\n    84 - you may read the canonical upstream artifact paths for the same `run_profile_id` and `prompt_id` when inferring the next missing condition\n    85 - do not read any sibling result files, directories, or unrelated experiment outputs\n    86 \n    87 If a required upstream artifact is missing, ask only for that missing artifact or path.\n    88 Do not ask the user to re-explain the whole experiment.\n    89 \n    90 ## 0.0.2 Canonical Artifact Resolution\n    91 \n    92 When deriving same-cell paths, use this canonical pattern:\n    93 \n    94 ```text\n    95 /tmp/duck_[MODEL_SLUG]_[REASONING_TIER]_[PROMPT_ID]_[CONDITION].md\n    96 ```\n    97 \n    98 Example for `claude_low / C01`:\n    99 - `/tmp/duck_claude-sonnet_low_C01_baseline.md`\n   100 - `/tmp/duck_claude-sonnet_low_C01_prompted.md`\n   101 - `/tmp/duck_claude-sonnet_low_C01_critique_initial.md`\n   102 - `/tmp/duck_claude-sonnet_low_C01_tool_review.md`\n   103 - `/tmp/duck_claude-sonnet_low_C01_critique_revised.md`\n   104 \n   105 Completion rules:\n   106 1. Resolve `model_slug` and `reasoning_tier` from the run profile catalog.\n   107 2. Build the five canonical same-cell paths for the current `run_profile_id` and `prompt_id`.\n   108 3. A response cell counts as complete only if the file exists and includes matching:\n   109    - `run_profile_id`\n   110    - `prompt_id`\n   111    - `condition`\n   112 4. A `tool_review` cell counts as complete only if the file exists and includes matching:\n   113    - `run_profile_id`\n   114    - `prompt_id`\n   115    - `condition: tool_review`\n   116    - `tool_environment_status: available`\n   117    - at least one CT-MCP tool actually 