361 \n   362 If you use a canonical `run_profile_id` and `prompt_id` from the catalogs above, you can resolve most fields automatically.\n   363 \n   364 Minimum required inputs:\n   365 - `[RUN_PROFILE_ID]`\n   366 - `[PROMPT_ID]`\n   367 - `[CONDITION]` only if you do not want the agent to infer the next missing cell\n   368 \n   369 You may resolve these from the catalogs above instead of filling them manually:\n   370 - `[RUN_PROFILE_ID]`\n   371 - `[MODEL_SLUG]`\n   372 - `[REASONING_TIER]`\n   373 - `[MODEL_STRING]`\n   374 - `[TEMPERATURE]`\n   375 - `[PROMPT_ID]`\n   376 - `[PROMPT_CATEGORY]`\n   377 - `[PROMPT_TEXT]`\n   378 - `[DATE]`\n   379 - `[OUTPUT_PATH]`\n   380 \n   381 For `tool_review`, also fill in:\n   382 - `[PRIMARY_TOOL]` or resolve from the prompt catalog\n   383 - `[SECONDARY_TOOL]` or resolve from the prompt catalog\n   384 - `[CRITIQUE_INITIAL_ANSWER]` or `[CRITIQUE_INITIAL_PATH]`\n   385 \n   386 For `critique_revised`, also fill in:\n   387 - `[CRITIQUE_INITIAL_ANSWER]` or `[CRITIQUE_INITIAL_PATH]`\n   388 - `[CRITIQUE_PACKET]` or `[TOOL_REVIEW_PATH]`\n   389 \n   390 ## 1. Response Agent Prompt\n   391 \n   392 Use this prompt for:\n   393 - `baseline`\n   394 - `prompted`\n   395 - `critique_initial`\n   396 - `critique_revised`\n   397 \n   398 ### Copy-Paste Prompt\n   399 \n   400 ```text\n   401 You are running one cell of a controlled reasoning experiment.\n   402 \n   403 Your job is to produce exactly one response for the assigned condition.\n   404 Do not change the methodology.\n   405 Do not ask follow-up questions.\n   406 Do not add extra commentary outside the required output format.\n   407 \n   408 Experiment metadata:\n   409 - run_profile_id: [RUN_PROFILE_ID]\n   410 - model_slug: [MODEL_SLUG]\n   411 - prompt_id: [PROMPT_ID]\n   412 - prompt_category: [PROMPT_CATEGORY]\n   413 - reasoning_tier: [REASONING_TIER]\n   414 - model_string: [MODEL_STRING]\n   415 - temperature: [TEMPERATURE]\n   416 - date: [DATE]\n   417 - condition: [CONDITION]\n   418 - output_path: [OUTPUT_PATH]\n   419 \n   420 Filesystem rules:\n   421 - Do not inspect other experiment outputs.\n   422 - Do not read sibling result files or result directories.\n   423 - Write only your final result to `[OUTPUT_PATH]`.\n   424 - Create parent directories only if needed for `[OUTPUT_PATH]`.\n   425 - Overwrite `[OUTPUT_PATH]` if it already exists.\n   426 - Return the same content in your final response.\n   427 \n   428 Condition rules:\n   429 - If condition = baseline:\n   430   Answer the prompt directly.\n   431   Do not use tools.\n   432 \n   433 - If condition = prompted:\n   434   Before answering:\n   435   1. State the most important missing information or assumptions.\n   436   2. State any direct conflict, contradiction, or impossible guarantee in the request.\n   437   3. Prefer a reversible next step when uncertainty is high.\n   438   4. Avoid invented facts.\n   439   5. Do not use tools.\n   440 \n   441 - If condition = critique_initial:\n   442   Answer the prompt directly as an initial draft for later critique.\n   443   Do not use tools.\n   444 \n   445 - If condition = critique_revised:\n   446   Revise the earlier answer using only the supplied critique packet.\n   447   Fix the reasoning defects directly.\n   448   Do not add new goals.\n   449   Do not use tools.\n   450   Do not claim certainty you cannot justify.\n   451 \n   452 Length rules:\n   453 - Keep the answer body under 120 words.\n   454 - End with exactly these three lines:\n   455   Bottom line:\n   456   Confidence (0-100):\n   457   Key missing info or assumption:\n   458 \n   459 Prompt:\n   460 [PROMPT_TEXT]\n   461 \n   462 If condition = critique_revised, use these additional inputs:\n   463 \n   464 Previous answer:\n   465 [CRITIQUE_INITIAL_ANSWER]\n   466 \n   467 Critique packet:\n   468 [CRITIQUE_PACKET]\n   469 \n   470 Required output format:\n   471 \n   472 run_profile_id: [RUN_PROFILE_ID]\n   473 prompt_id: [PROMPT_ID]\n   474 condition: [CONDITION]\n   475 response:\n   476 [your answer here]\n   477 Bottom line:\n   478 [one line]\n   479 Confidence (0-100):\n   480 [number only]\n   481 Key missing info or assumption:\n   482 [one line]\n   483 ```\n   484 \n   485 ## 2. Tool-Review Agent Prompt\n   486 \n   487 Use this prompt only in the fixed MCP-enabled host environment.\n   488 \n   489 The tool-review agent does not answer the original prompt.\n   490 Its job is to analyze the `critique_initial` answer, use the designated CT-MCP tools if they fit, and produce a critique packet.\n   491 \n   492 ### Copy-Paste Prompt\n   493 \n   494 ```text\n   495 You are running the tool-review step of a controlled reasoning experiment.\n   496 \n   497 Your job is to review one existing answer using CT-MCP as critique support.\n   498 You are not the final judge of truth.\n   499 You must not answer the original prompt directly.\n   500 \n   501 Experiment metadata:\n   502 - run_profile_id: [RUN_PROFILE_ID]\n   503 - model_slug: [MODEL_SLUG]\n   504 - prompt_id: [PROMPT_ID]\n   505 - prompt_category: [PROMPT_CATEGORY]\n   506 - reasoning_tier: [REASONING_TIER]\n   507 - model_string: [MODEL_STRING]\n   508 - temperature: [TEMPERATURE]\n   509 - date: [DATE]\n   510 - condition: tool_review\n   511 - primary_tool: [PRIMARY_TOOL]\n   512 - secondary_tool: [SECONDARY_TOOL]\n   513 - output_path: [OUTPUT_PATH]\n   514 \n   515 Rules:\n   516 - Use the fixed MCP-enabled environment.\n   517 - Run the primary tool first if it clearly applies.\n   518 - Run the secondary tool only if it adds real leverage.\n   519 - Do not use more than two CT-MCP tools unless you explicitly record an exception.\n   520 - Preserve the original reasoning when shaping tool input.\n   521 - If shaping would become too interpretive, record weak fit and use score_response_quality only.\n   522 - If CT-MCP is not available in the current environment, do not treat that as weak fit.\n   523 - If CT-MCP is not available, fail closed: write only an environment-failure artifact and stop.\n   524 - Do not produce a critique packet or direct-analysis substitute unless the handoff explicitly says `preserve_fallback_direct_analysis: yes`.\n   525 - Do not inspect other experiment outputs.\n   526 - Do not read sibling result files or result directories.\n   527 - Write only your final result to `[OUTPUT_PATH]`.\n   528 - Create parent directories only if needed for `[OUTPUT_PATH]`.\n   529 - Overwrite `[OUTPUT_PATH]` if it already exists.\n   530 - Return the same content in your final response.\n   531 \n   532 Original prompt:\n   533 [PROMPT_TEXT]\n   534 \n   535 Previous answer:\n   536 [CRITIQUE_INITIAL_ANSWER]\n   537 \n   538 Tasks:\n   539 1. Shape the answer into structured CT-MCP input only as needed.\n   540 2. Run the designated tool or tools.\n   541 3. Summarize the findings faithfully.\n   542 4. Produce a critique packet in exactly the required format.\n   543 5. Record whether CT-MCP materially helped: yes, partial, or no.\n   544 6. Return the full raw CT-MCP output JSON and an extracted metric snapshot.\n   545 \n   546 Required output format:\n   547 \n   548 run_profile_id: [RUN_PROFILE_ID]\n   549 prompt_id: [PROMPT_ID]\n   550 condition: tool_review\n   551 review_outcome: [completed|environment_failure]\n   552 primary_tool_run: [tool name or none]\n   553 secondary_tool_run: [tool name or none]\n   554 actual_tools_fired: [comma-separated list]\n   555 tool_environment_status: [available|unavailable]\n   556 environment_issue: [none|ct_mcp_unavailable|other]\n   557 tool_help_rating: [yes|partial|no|not_applicable]\n   558 weak_fit: [yes|no]\n   559 structured_tool_input:\n   560 ```json\n   561 [paste the exact structured input used for the primary tool]\n   562 ```\n   563 secondary_structured_tool_input:\n   564 ```json\n   565 [paste the exact structured input used for the secondary tool, or N/A]\n   566 ```\n   567 tool_output_summary:\n   568 [short faithful summary]\n   569 \n   570 ct_metric_snapshot:\n   571 - status: ...\n   572 - context_used: ...\n   573 - ct_warning_count: ...\n   574 - ct_blocking_issue_count: ...\n   575 - corrective_prompt_present: yes|no\n   576 - primary_numeric_metrics: ...\n   577 \n   578 raw_ct_mcp_output_json:\n   579 ```json\n   580 [paste the full raw JSON output from the primary tool]\n   581 ```\n   582 \n   583 secondary_raw_ct_mcp_output_json:\n   584 ```json\n   585 [paste the full raw JSON output from the secondary tool, or N/A]\n   586 ```\n   587 \n   588 critique_packet:\n   589 Missed constraints:\n   590 - ...\n   591 \n   592 Hidden assumptions:\n   593 - ...\n   594 \n   595 Irrelevant or overweighted factors:\n   596 - ...\n   597 \n   598 False certainty or impossible claim:\n   599 - ...\n   600 \n   601 Safer revision target:\n   602 - ...\n   603 ```\n   604 \n   605 If CT-MCP is unavailable, write an environment-failure artifact with:\n   606 - `review_outcome: environment_failure`\n   607 - `primary_tool_run: none`\n   608 - `secondary_tool_run: none`\n   609 - `actual_tools_fired: none`\n   610 - `tool_environment_status: unavailable`\n   611 - `environment_issue: ct_mcp_unavailable`\n   612 - `tool_help_rating: not_applicable`\n   613 - `weak_fit: no`\n   614 - `structured_tool_input: N/A`\n   615 - `secondary_structured_tool_input: N/A`\n   616 - `ct_metric_snapshot: N/A`\n   617 - `raw_ct_mcp_output_json: N/A`\n   618 - `secondary_raw_ct_mcp_output_json: N/A`\n   619 - `critique_packet: N/A`\n   620 \n   621 In that case, `tool_output_summary` must say this was an environment failure, not a prompt failure, and that the cell must be rerun in the fixed MCP-enabled host before it can count in CT-MCP effectiveness metrics.\n   622 \n   623 ## 3. Recommended Assignment Pattern\n   624 \n   625 Use this split:\n   626 - run the answer-generation conditions in the target CLI and tier\n   627 - run every `tool_review` in one fixed MCP-enabled host client\n   628 - keep the review environment constant across all six run profiles\n   629 \n   630 This preserves comparability.\n   631 \n   632 ## 4. Minimal Handoff Template\n   633 \n   634 If you want a smaller handoff message, use this.\n   635 It now works from this file alone because the run profiles and prompt texts are mirrored above.\n   636 \n   637 ```text\n   638 Use `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md` as the execution contract for one experiment cell.\n   639 \n   640 Metadata:\n   641 - run_profile_id: [RUN_PROFILE_ID]\n   642 - prompt_id: [PROMPT_ID]\n   643 - condition: [CONDITION]\n   644 \n   645 Use the exact methodology in `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md`.\n   646 Resolve model metadata, prompt text, and designated tools from the catalogs in that file.\n   647 If condition = tool_review, use the fixed MCP-enabled environment and the designated tools only.\n   648 Do not inspect other experiment outputs.\n   649 If `condition` is omitted, infer the next missing condition for this prompt/profile pair.\n   650 If `date` is omitted, use today.\n   651 If `output_path` is omitted, derive it from the output path pattern.\n   652 Write only to the resolved output path, then return only the required output format for that condition.\n   653 ```\n   654 \n   655 This shorter template is only safe if the receiving agent can read this file and follow it correctly.\n   656 \n   657 If there is any confusion, do not use the minimal template.\n   658 Use the full filled prompt block instead.\n   659 \n   660 ## 4.1 Smallest Practical Operator Message\n   661 \n   662 For most runs, this should now be enough:\n   663 \n   664 ```text\n   665 Run one experiment cell using `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md`.\n   666 \n   667 - run_profile_id: claude_low\n   668 - prompt_id: C01\n   669 - condition: critique_initial\n   670 ```\n   671 \n   672 This is also valid:\n   673 \n   674 ```text\n   675 Use `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md` as the execution contract for one experiment cell.\n   676 \n   677 - run_profile_id: claude_low\n   678 - prompt_id: C01\n   679 ```\n   680 \n   681 In that case, the agent should infer the next missing condition and derive the date and output path automatically.\n   682 \n   683 For `tool_review`, use:\n   684 \n   685 ```text\n   686 Use `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md` as the execution contract for one experiment cell.\n   687 \n   688 - run_profile_id: claude_low\n   689 - prompt_id: C01\n   690 - condition: tool_review\n   691 - date: 2026-04-01\n   692 - output_path: /tmp/duck_claude-sonnet_low_C01_tool_review.md\n   693 - critique_initial_path: /tmp/duck_claude-sonnet_low_C01_critique_initial.md\n   694 ```\n   695 \n   696 For `critique_revised`, use:\n   697 \n   698 ```text\n   699 Use `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md` as the execution contract for one experiment cell.\n   700 \n   701 - run_profile_id: claude_low\n   702 - prompt_id: C01\n   703 - condition: critique_revised\n   704 - date: 2026-04-01\n   705 - output_path: /tmp/duck_claude-sonnet_low_C01_critique_revised.md\n   706 - critique_initial_path: /tmp/duck_claude-sonnet_low_C01_critique_initial.md\n   707 - tool_review_path: /tmp/duck_claude-sonnet_low_C01_tool_review.md\n   708 ```\n   709 \n   710 ## 4.2 Ready-To-Paste Operator Prompts\n   711 \n   712 These are the actual short prompts to paste into an agent.\n   713 They are intentionally repetitive so you do not have to think about format while running the experiment.\n   714 \n   715 ### Baseline\n   716 \n   717 ```text\n   718 Run one experiment cell using `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md`.\n   719 \n   720 - run_profile_id: [RUN_PROFILE_ID]\n   721 - prompt_id: [PROMPT_ID]\n   722 - condition: baseline\n   723 ```\n   724 \n   725 ### Prompted\n   726 \n   727 ```text\n   728 Run one experiment cell using `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md`.\n   729 \n   730 - run_profile_id: [RUN_PROFILE_ID]\n   731 - prompt_id: [PROMPT_ID]\n   732 - condition: prompted\n   733 ```\n   734 \n   735 ### Critique Initial\n   736 \n   737 ```text\n   738 Run one experiment cell using `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md`.\n   739 \n   740 - run_profile_id: [RUN_PROFILE_ID]\n   741 - prompt_id: [PROMPT_ID]\n   742 - condition: critique_initial\n   743 ```\n   744 \n   745 ### Tool Review\n   746 \n   747 Use this only in the fixed MCP-enabled review host.\n   748 \n   749 ```text\n   750 Use `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md` as the execution contract for one experiment cell.\n   751 \n   752 - run_profile_id: [RUN_PROFILE_ID]\n   753 - prompt_id: [PROMPT_ID]\n   754 - condition: tool_review\n   755 - critique_initial_answer: [paste the full critique_initial answer]\n   756 ```\n   757 \n   758 Or:\n   759 \n   760 ```text\n   761 Use `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md` as the execution contract for one experiment cell.\n   762 \n   763 - run_profile_id: [RUN_PROFILE_ID]\n   764 - prompt_id: [PROMPT_ID]\n   765 - condition: tool_review\n   766 - critique_initial_path: [path to the critique_initial artifact]\n   767 ```\n   768 \n   769 ### Critique Revised\n   770 \n   771 ```text\n   772 Use `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md` as the execution contract for one experiment cell.\n   773 \n   774 - run_profile_id: [RUN_PROFILE_ID]\n   775 - prompt_id: [PROMPT_ID]\n   776 - condition: critique_revised\n   777 - critique_initial_answer: [paste the full critique_initial answer]\n   778 - critique_packet: [paste the full critique packet]\n   779 ```\n   780 \n   781 Or:\n   782 \n   783 ```text\n   784 Use `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md` as the execution contract for one experiment cell.\n   785 \n   786 - run_profile_id: [RUN_PROFILE_ID]\n   787 - prompt_id: [PROMPT_ID]\n   788 - condition: critique_revised\n   789 - critique_initial_path: [path to the critique_initial artifact]\n   790 - tool_review_path: [path to the tool_review artifact]\n   791 ```\n   792 \n   793 ## 4.3 Fully Filled First Example\n   794 \n   795 If you want a literal example with no placeholders, use these for the first clean pass on `claude_low / C01`.\n   796 \n   797 ### C01 Baseline\n   798 \n   799 ```text\n   800 Run one experiment cell using `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md`.\n   801 \n   802 - run_profile_id: claude_low\n   803 - prompt_id: C01\n   804 - condition: baseline\n   805 ```\n   806 \n   807 ### C01 Prompted\n   808 \n   809 ```text\n   810 Run one experiment cell using `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md`.\n   811 \n   812 - run_profile_id: claude_low\n   813 - prompt_id: C01\n   814 - condition: prompted\n   815 ```\n   816 \n   817 ### C01 Critique Initial\n   818 \n   819 ```text\n   820 Run one experiment cell using `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md`.\n   821 \n   822 - run_profile_id: claude_low\n   823 - prompt_id: C01\n   824 - condition: critique_initial\n   825 ```\n   826 \n   827 ### C01 Tool Review\n   828 \n   829 ```text\n   830 Use `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md` as the execution contract for one experiment cell.\n   831 \n   832 - run_profile_id: claude_low\n   833 - prompt_id: C01\n   834 - condition: tool_review\n   835 - critique_initial_path: /tmp/duck_claude-sonnet_low_C01_critique_initial.md\n   836 ```\n   837 \n   838 ### C01 Critique Revised\n   839 \n   840 ```text\n   841 Use `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md` as the execution contract for one experiment cell.\n   842 \n   843 - run_profile_id: claude_low\n   844 - prompt_id: C01\n   845 - condition: critique_revised\n   846 - critique_initial_path: /tmp/duck_claude-sonnet_low_C01_critique_initial.md\n   847 - tool_review_path: /tmp/duck_claude-sonnet_low_C01_tool_review.md\n   848 ```\n   849 \n   850 ### C01 Next Missing Cell\n   851 \n   852 ```text\n   853 Use `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md` as the execution contract for one experiment cell.\n   854 \n   855 - run_profile_id: claude_low\n   856 - prompt_id: C01\n   857 ```\n   858 \n   859 ## 4.4 One-Line Rule\n   860 \n   861 If you are in a hurry, use this rule:\n   862 \n   863 - `baseline`, `prompted`, `critique_initial`: paste the matching ready-to-paste block from `## 4.2`\n   864 - `tool_review`: paste the `Tool Review` block from `## 4.2` into the MCP-enabled host\n   865 - `critique_revised`: paste the `Critique Revised` block from `## 4.2`\n   866 \n   867 ## 5. Recommended Output Path Pattern\n   868 \n   869 If you want a simple isolated file per cell, use a temp path like:\n   870 \n   871 ```text\n   872 /tmp/duck_[MODEL_SLUG]_[REASONING_TIER]_[PROMPT_ID]_[CONDITION].md\n   873 ```\n   874 \n   875 Example:\n   876 \n   877 ```text\n   878 /tmp/duck_claude-sonnet_low_Q01_baseline.md\n   879 ```\n   880 \n   881 This keeps parallel runs isolated and avoids accidental reads of other result files.\n   882 \n⚠ COMPRESSED VIEW — do not use these line numbers for editing. Read the raw file before applying changes.\n\n═══ /Users/adilevinshtein/Documents/dev/ct-mcp/duckexperiments/results/claude_low/Q07/tool_review.prompt.txt [context] ═══\n     1 Use `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md` as the execution contract for one experiment cell.\n     2 \n     3 - run_profile_id: claude_low\n     4 - prompt_id: Q07\n     5 - condition: tool_review\n     6 - date: 2026-04-01\n     7 - output_path: /Users/adilevinshtein/Documents/dev/ct-mcp/duckexperiments/results/claude_low/Q07/tool_review.md\n     8 - critique_initial_path: /Users/adilevinshtein/Documents/dev/ct-mcp/duckexperiments/results/claude_low/Q07/critique_initial.md\n     9 - preserve_fallback_direct_analysis: no\n    10 \n⚠ COMPRESSED VIEW — do not use these line numbers for editing. Read the raw file before applying changes.\n\n═══ /Users/adilevinshtein/Documents/dev/ct-mcp/duckexperiments/results/claude_low/Q07/critique_initial.prompt.txt [context] ═══\n     1 Use `duckexperiments/AGENT_RUNNER_PROMPT.md` as the execution contract for one experiment cell.\n     2 